Postoperative discomfort (D): Through air spray for 5 s over the operated site, sensitive function was measured at 7, 14, and 28 days after surgical procedure. After air spray application, patients were required to use a visual analogue scale (VAS) of 100 mm to assess discomfort; scale extremes were “no pain” to “extreme.” In addition, patients were asked to report the number of analgesics taken during the first week [13].
